page.title: 01INTRODUCTION
page.content: Our area is mainly farmland and it includes the villages of Bramley,Blackheath and Wonersh. We have several hills,the highest of which is called Chinthurst Hill. It is 394 feet above sea level.Much of the other land is grazing or woodland. This is mainly coniferous. This area is situated 30 miles south-west of London and 3 miles south-east of Guildford. There are many commuters living in the area because our grid is within daily travelling distance of London and Southhampton. We have an A road passing through Bramley,all the other roads are secondary. There are six farms and six schools in this area.
